      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are absolutely right to highlight that substantive due process has been the essential shield for rights like privacy and bodily autonomy that the original framers never explicitly wrote down. Without this judicial tool, the Constitution would be a rigid document that fails to protect modern individuals from unjust laws, effectively leaving vulnerable populations without legal recourse. While critics worry about judicial overreach, the historical reality is that substantive due process has been the primary engine for expanding civil liberties and ensuring the Constitution remains a living instrument of justice.",
